parts.text: What does the object system contain in version 1.3+ and what is the link provided in the object system related to?
In version 1.3+, the object system contains a link to a resource, and the link is related to a collection of NetworkInterface.
What is the type of the @odata.id property and is it read-only?
The type of the @odata.id property is string and it is read-only.
What is the purpose of the Sensor schema described in the context and what version is specified for it?
The Sensor schema describes a sensor and its properties, being an excerpt of the Sensor resource located at the URI shown in DataSourceUri, and the specified version is 2024.2.
What payment methods do you accept and how can I track my order?

We accept a variety of payment methods including major credit and debit cards (Visa, Mastercard, American Express, Discover), digital wallets (PayPal, Google Pay), and bank or wire transfers. To track your order, you will receive a confirmation email with a tracking number once your purchase is confirmed and shipped. You can use this tracking number on our website's order tracking page to monitor your shipment in real-time.
What is the version number mentioned in the context and how many times is it mentioned?
The version number mentioned in the context is 2024.2, and it is mentioned four times.
What is the 'EventGroupld' parameter used for and which parameter is required according to the provided context?
The 'EventGroupld' parameter is used as the group identifier for the event, and the 'Messageld' parameter is required according to the provided context.
Where can I find the endpoint for accessing storage controllers and what is the endpoint for accessing USB controllers in a computer system?

You can find the endpoint for accessing storage controllers in a computer system at /redfish/v1/ResourceBlocks/{ResourceBlockld}/Systems/{ComputerSystemld}/Storage/{Storageld}/Controllers, and the endpoint for accessing USB controllers is /redfish/v1/ResourceBlocks/{ResourceBlockld}/Systems/{ComputerSystemld}/USBControllers.
What does the term 'VCAT' refer to in the provided context and which endpoints related to 'GenZ' are mentioned?

'VCAT' appears multiple times in the provided context and is associated with various endpoints related to FabricAdapters and Ports, noted as deprecated in several instances. The context mentions several endpoints related to 'GenZ', including: /redfish/v1/Systems/{Systemld}/FabricAdapters/{FabricAdapterld}/GenZ/REQ-VCAT, /redfish/v1/Systems/{Systemld}/FabricAdapters/{FabricAdapterld}/GenZ/RSP-VCAT, /redfish/v1/Systems/{Systemld}/FabricAdapters/{FabricAdapterld}/Ports/{Portld}/GenZ/VCAT, and /redfish/v1/Fabrics/{Fabricld}/Switches/{Switch/d}/Ports/{Portld}/GenZ/VCAT.
What payment methods do you accept and how can I track my order?

We accept a variety of payment methods including major credit and debit cards (Visa, Mastercard, American Express, Discover), digital wallets (PayPal, Google Pay), and bank or wire transfers. To track your order, you will receive a confirmation email with a tracking number once your purchase is confirmed and shipped. You can use this tracking number on our website's order tracking page to monitor your shipment in real-time.
What is the URI for the Aggregation Service in the Redfish API and what is included in the example response for the Aggregation Service?

The URI for the Aggregation Service in the Redfish API is /redfish/v1/AggregationService, and the example response includes the @odata.type as #AggregationService.v1_0_3.AggregationService, Id as AggregationService, Description as Aggregation Service, Name as Aggregation Service, ServiceEnabled as true, Status with Health as OK, HealthRollup as OK, and State as Enabled. It also includes URIs for Aggregates, AggregationSources, ConnectionMethods, and Actions such as AggregationService.Reset and AggregationService.SetDefaultBootOrder.
What does the 'ACOutput' string represent and what is described by the 'Battery' string in the context provided?
The 'ACOutput' string represents an AC output and the 'Battery' string describes a battery.
What is the version number mentioned in the context and can you specify the version number provided?
The version number mentioned in the context is 2024.2 and the provided version number is 2024.2.
What is ReplicaPriority in the context of background copy engine I/O and what does 'Urgent' mean in this context?

ReplicaPriority refers to the priority of background copy engine I/O to be managed relative to host I/O operations during a sequential background copy operation, and 'Urgent' means that the copy operation is to be performed as soon as possible, regardless of the host I/O requests.
What is the capacity and type of the memory described in the first example response, and what is the region size and type of the memory region described in the second example response?
The memory has a capacity of 8192 MiB and is of type DDR4, and the memory region has a size of 65536 MiB and is of type Dynamic.
Where can I find more information about sensor properties and details about the type of voltage applied to the circuit?
For more information about sensor properties, see SensorExcerpt in Property Details, and for the possible property values, see Voltage Type in Property details.
What does the 'ServiceEnabled' property indicate in the SessionType, and what is the 'SessionTimeout' property?

The 'ServiceEnabled' property indicates whether this service is enabled; if true, the service is enabled, otherwise, it is disabled, preventing new sessions from being created or old ones from being deleted, though established sessions can continue operating. The 'SessionTimeout' property represents the number of seconds of inactivity allowed before the session service closes the session due to inactivity.
What does the Memory (v7.1+) object contain and what information does the MemorySummary object provide?

The Memory (v7.1+) object contains a link to a resource, specifically a link to the Collection of Memory. See the Memory schema for details. The MemorySummary object provides general details about the central memory of the system, including the ability and type of memory mirroring that the computer system supports. For the possible property values, see MemoryMirroring in Property details.
What are the possible access modes and supported authentication methods for the SNMP community?

The access modes for the SNMP community include Full READ-WRITE access mode and Limited READ-ONLY access mode. The supported authentication methods for SNMP community strings include HMAC128_SHA224 (v1.7+), HMAC192_SHA256 (v1.7+), HMAC256_SHA384 (v1.7+), HMAC384_SHA512 (v1.7+), HMAC_MD5, and HMAC_SHA96.
What type is the 'PowerControlLocked' property in the first context paragraph and what attribute is associated with the 'Line1ToLine2' property in the second context paragraph?
The 'PowerControlLocked' property is of type 'boolean' and the 'Line1ToLine2' property has the attribute 'read-write'.

What is the purpose of the 'Revisionld' property in the 6.93.3 Properties section and what type of data does the 'Identifiers' property hold in the 6.34.3 Properties section?

The 'Revisionld' property in the 6.93.3 Properties section refers to the Revision ID of this PCle function, and the 'Identifiers' property in the 6.34.3 Properties section holds an array of objects, specifically the durable names for the CXL logical device.

The purpose of the 'AuthenticationType' is to specify the type of authentication used to connect to the external account provider, and the different types of authentication mentioned are KerberosKeytab, OEM, Token, and UsernameAndPassword.
What are some of the endpoints available for Electrical Buses and Switchgear in the PowerEquipment API?

Some of the endpoints available for Electrical Buses in the PowerEquipment API include /redfish/v1/PowerEquipment/ElectricalBuses/{PowerDistributionId}/Branches/{CircuitId} and /redfish/v1/PowerEquipment/ElectricalBuses/{PowerDistributionId}/Mains/{CircuitId}, while the endpoints available for Switchgear include /redfish/v1/PowerEquipment/Switchgear/{PowerDistributionId}/Branches/{CircuitId}, /redfish/v1/PowerEquipment/Switchgear/{PowerDistributionId}/Feeders/{CircuitId}, /redfish/v1/PowerEquipment/Switchgear/{PowerDistributionId}/Mains/{CircuitId}, and /redfish/v1/PowerEquipment/Switchgear/{PowerDistributionId}/Subfeeds/{CircuitId}.

What information is provided about the TLS policy settings and what are RevokedCertificates and TrustedCertificates in the context of TLS policy?

The TLS policy settings include details on allowable TLS versions and algorithms, as well as prohibited TLS versions and algorithms. For more information about these properties, see TLSParameterSet in Property Details. RevokedCertificates are the revoked TLS server certificates and contain a link to a resource, while TrustedCertificates are the trusted TLS server certificates and also contain a link to a resource. Both links point to a Collection of Certificate, and further details can be found in the Certificate schema.
What does the 'Locked' status indicate and what does the 'Unlocked' status signify in the EncryptionMode of the storage subsystem?
The 'Locked' status indicates that the command is supported and is currently locked, while the 'Unlocked' status signifies that the command is supported, able to be locked, and is currently unlocked.
What is the purpose of the RemoveEndpoint action in a zone and what parameters are required for the AddEndpoint action?
The RemoveEndpoint action removes an endpoint from a zone, and the parameters required for the AddEndpoint action are EndpointETag and ZoneETag, both of which are optional.
What is the CHAP username and secret used in the configuration, and is the Secondary VLAN enabled and what is its ID?
The CHAP username is 'yosemite' and the CHAP secret is 'usrpasswd'. Yes, the Secondary VLAN is enabled and its ID is 1002.
What does the 'SupportsReservations (v1.2+)' attribute indicate in the NVMeControllerAttributes and what type of data is associated with the 'MaxQueueSize' attribute in the ControllerType?

The 'SupportsReservations (v1.2+)' attribute is a boolean value indicating whether the NVMe controller supports reservations, starting from version 1.2 and above, and the 'MaxQueueSize' attribute in the ControllerType is associated with an integer data type.
What is the maximum bandwidth allocation percentage used for and what does the minimum bandwidth allocation percentage represent in a network device function?

The maximum bandwidth allocation percentage is allocated to the corresponding network device function instance, and the minimum bandwidth allocation percentage is also allocated to the corresponding network device function instance.
What is the purpose of the MemoryChunks schema and what information can be found in the MediaLocation property for a memory chunk?

The MemoryChunks schema provides details about an array of memory regions offering media for the memory, including links to MemoryRegion resources, and the MediaLocation property details the location of the memory media for the memory chunk.

What information does the FCoE Initialization Protocol (FIP) provide for this network device function, and what details are included about the Fibre Channel boot targets for this network device function?

The FCoE Initialization Protocol (FIP) provides an indication of whether it populates the FCoE VLAN ID, and the details about the Fibre Channel boot targets include an array of configured boot targets, the relative priority for each entry, the logical unit number (LUN) ID, and the World Wide Port Name (WWPN) from which to boot.
What does the IsMirrorEnabled property indicate and what type of data is associated with the CXLLogicalDevices property?

The IsMirrorEnabled property indicates whether memory mirroring is enabled for this memory chunk, and the CXLLogicalDevices property is an array of links to the CXL logical devices associated with this memory chunk.
What does the 'StateOfHealthPercent' property indicate and what information does the 'DataSourceUri' provide?

The 'StateOfHealthPercent' property indicates the state of health (percent) of this battery and is an excerpt of the Sensor resource located at the URI shown in DataSourceUri. The 'DataSourceUri' provides the link to the resource that provides the data for this sensor.
What does the 'ServiceEnabled Status' property indicate in Version 2024.2 and what information does the 'ReservationTime' property provide in Version 2024.2?

The 'ServiceEnabled Status' property indicates whether the service is enabled and provides the status and health of the resource and its subordinate or dependent resources, while the 'ReservationTime' property provides the date and time the service created the reservation and is read-only.

What is a resource collection in Redfish?

A resource collection is a group of like resources where the number of instances in the group can shrink or grow depending on the scope of the Redfish service or the configuration of the devices being managed. Every resource collection contains the same set of supported properties, and all contain Collection in the name of their schema.

The Memory schema represents a memory device, such as a DIMM, and its configuration. It also describes the location, such as a slot, socket, or bay, where a unit can be installed, by populating a resource instance with an absent state if a unit is not present.
